snippet.textDisplay:
Just saying it’s illegal to make decisions based on someone’s race but in many places in the US it’s not illegal to make decisions based on someone’s sexual orientation.

So even if there are racist individuals alive at least it’s not legal for them to deny you an apartment or a job because you are black yet for anyone LGBTQ+ you can deny them a home or a job and tell them it’s because they’re LGBTQ+ and there will be no repercussions legally in many parts of the US.

Also just saying in the black community there is rampant generational homophobia yet they don’t want people to be racist against them. This is just some of the reasons I have little to no empathy for modern day black community struggles when legally they have the same rights.

Honestly for black people it’s just a waiting game which is going to take a few generations so all the old racists can die off and the younger black generations can take action to persue leadership roles across the US in all areas.
